 large families increasing the population to say 1200, there is only so much knowledge they can absorb from DVD's. It will have to be the most essential stuff. More advanced science and engineering would be useless before the manpower exists to exploit it. They should know it exists but not be distracted by it. Too much knowledge can be bad. How would we feel if the secret to warp drive engines existed right in front of us but was so complex and advanced only a civilisation of 50 billion could support such a technology? Pretty devastated I imagine. It's doubtful the Earth could support that many human beings for a start. You could give the plans and detailed instructions on everything necessary to build a car to cavemen but it wont get you a car. A small tribe cannot withdraw enough labour away from hunting and gathering to learn it all then carry it out.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=89.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=89.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=89.topic&start=61&stop=74>4</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showPrevMessage?topicID=89.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showNextMessage?topicID=89.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=60><img src=http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/addreply3.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.emailToFriend?topicID=89.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/i